Display an Enhanced Link in an Enhanced Bot

Send a customized, interactive web page link over your enhanced channels with the enhanced link messaging component.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Before you begin:

From the Messaging Component page in Setup, create an enhanced link messaging component.
If you’ve added parameters to your messaging component to use dynamic inputs to customize your enhanced link, create an Apex class or flow to generate session-specific inputs.

From the Einstein Bots Setup page, select the bot you want to use to send an enhanced link.
From the Bot Builder, click Dialogs, and then select the dialog that you want to use to send an enhanced link.

If you’ve added parameters to your messaging component to customize your enhanced link, add an Apex class or flow to your dialog.
Drag the Apex or Flow action dialog step onto the canvas.
Select the Apex class or flow associated with the enhanced link component.
Create or select a bot variable to store the output of the Apex class or flow.

Drag the Enhanced Link dialog step onto the canvas.
Enter the name of your messaging component to search for and select it.
If you’ve added parameters to your messaging component to customize your enhanced link, for each input parameter, specify a bot variable.

Save your changes.
